<h3>Hidden Stylish preferences</h3>

<p>Stylish has preferences to customize its behaviour which are not exposed to the UI. These prefs can be changed in about:config.</p>
<dl>
	<dt>extensions.stylish.dbFile</dt>
	<dd>Path to the stylish.sqlite database which stores installed style info. Default is blank, meaning look for "stylish.sqlite" in the profile folder.</dd>
	<dt>extensions.stylish.editor</dt>
	<dd>Text editor to use when editing styles. 0 - Orion (with syntax highlighting) (default), 1 - plain old textbox. Orion is not available in all applications and versions.</dd>
	<dt>extensions.stylish.install.allowedDomains</dt>
	<dd>Space-seperated list of domains that can bring up install boxes and detect style install status. Default: userstyles.org.</dd>
	<dt>extensions.stylish.manageView</dt>
	<dd>Default manage interface. 0 - add-ons dialog (default), 1 - stand-alone dialog, 2 - sidebar. Add-ons dialog is not available in all applications and versions.</dd>
	<dt>extensions.stylish.promptOnInstall</dt>
	<dd>Whether to prompt before installing a style. Default: true.</dd>
	<dt>extensions.stylish.updatesEnabled</dt>
	<dd>Whether to check for updates for styles. Default: true.</dd>
</dl>

